author: National Geographic
description: In Hawaii, National Geographic photographer and anthropologist Josh Cogan and Joey, a man living with CIDP (chronic inflammatory demyelinating polyneuropathy), experience the importance of community as a pathway to helping us understand ourselves better and finding hope in people's individual journeys.

author: National Geographic
description:
Join National Geographic and investigate devastating Atlantic storms, including Hurricane Humberto and Hurricane Dorian, in this Gathering Storm MEGA Episode. Featuring three full episodes:  

The Cold Ocean Killer
Our cameras ride with the boats along America’s Northeast as they risk giant winter storms and rogue waves during a deadly Atlantic fishing season.  

Hurricane Humberto
Category 3 Hurricane Humberto veers away from the U.S. coast, heading directly toward the island of Bermuda. This is what our 1,000 cameras captured. 

Hurricane Dorian
Category 5 monster Hurricane Dorian tears through the Caribbean and the U.S. Eastern Seaboard. This is what our 1,000 cameras captured.
